Quote:  The <i>hokio</i>, says Williams, is 'the messenger bird'. <i>Hokio</i>, the verb 'to descend', is also 'a bird, probably the same as <i>hokioi</i>, with variant spellings of <i>hakuai</i> and <i>hokiwai</i> ... an extint bird of nocturnal habits, held in superstitious regard by the Maori, said to be never seen.
